Another issue is of course, you're giving up DPS by wearing the shield, making the fight that much longer. Assuming you have good dual wield/double attack skills, and a decent off-hand weapon(I know you do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ), you'll be giving up , let's say... one third of your damage output or so? The fight will last longer as a result, and you will suffer more hits accordingly. Not sure you'll take any less damage with the shield, I'd actually guess the opposite.<br>
Look at warriors - I know of no warrior wearing a shield when tanking.<br>
As a rogue, I'd avoid rolling on any shield (except Lodizal <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p>Bippin Tenderfoot <BR>
