Syll, need is always determined by utility over time for the character or class.  That shield may have all/all written on it, but as far as rolling goes, it should be pal/sk only.  Just like dragon bags are all/all, but are really monk-only as far as awarding (anyone else will just sell it to a monk and buy two tinks).  I've heard every song&amp;dance under the sun about how some character has some particular use that makes them special and thus deserving of rolling on an item that has obvious vastly greater utility for another class or character.  But, that's all it is.  Just singing dancing greed in sheep's clothing.  Well, maybe lamb's clothing.  It's a minor greed.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
